quotes.quote: When you're ten, they call you a prodigy. When you're fifteen, they call you a genius. Once you hit twenty, you're just an ordinary person.
No amount of natural talent trumps hard work.
I've seen this before. This sensation... I get it now. This is what I wanted. No need to rely on or work with other people. I just want to drift through the water alone in silence.
It works better if you don't try as hard, just like in real life.
